abstract: >-
  Core data model for Digital Material Passports (DMPs) defining material identity
  via chemical identifiers (CAS, InChI, InChIKey, SMILES), specification codes,
  commodity codes, and batch traceability. Includes supplier information, import/export
  compliance, and material specifications (composition, purity, physical/mechanical/thermal/
  chemical properties, fingerprinting, and test conditions). Integrates standard ontologies
  (ChEBI, ChemInf, CAS, UNSPSC, QUDT, EMMO, PATO, CHMO, OBI, Schema.org, GS1).
